name: NH7 Weekender 2025 Pune
description: One of India's largest multi-genre music festivals, featuring a diverse lineup of Indian and international artists across several stages. A celebration of music, art, and culture.

name: Mumbai Comic Con 2025
description: The ultimate pop-culture celebration in Mumbai. Features comics, movies, gaming, and cosplay. A chance to meet creators, buy merchandise, and enjoy interactive experiences.

name: India Art Fair 2025
description: South Asia's leading fair for modern and contemporary art. Showcasing a wide range of paintings, sculptures, photography, and digital art from Indian and international artists.

name: Jaipur Literature Festival (JLF) Warm-up
description: A pre-festival event featuring readings and discussions with prominent authors, part of the build-up to the main 'greatest literary show on Earth' in January.

name: Bangalore Tech Summit
description: Asia's largest technology event, congregating global tech leaders, innovators, researchers, and startups. Focuses on areas like AI, biotech, and future mobility.

name: Hyderabad Design Week
description: A city-wide festival celebrating design and innovation. Includes workshops, exhibitions, and talks on product design, fashion design, and urban planning.

name: Kolkata International Film Festival (KIFF)
description: An acclaimed annual film festival showcasing a curated selection of international and Indian cinema, with screenings, masterclasses, and filmmaker interactions.

name: Startup India Innovation Week
description: A national event for India's startup ecosystem, with sessions and workshops being held across major hubs like Bangalore. Focuses on funding, scaling, and policy.

name: Chennai Music Season (Margazhi)
description: One of the world's largest cultural events. Features thousands of Carnatic music and classical dance performances in various sabhas across the city.

name: Delhi Half Marathon
description: A prestigious annual road running event. Attracts international elite runners as well as thousands of amateur participants from across the country.

name: Lucknow Farmers Market
description: A weekly market promoting organic and local produce. A great place for the community to connect with farmers, artisans, and enjoy healthy food.

name: TiE Global Summit
description: A major conference for entrepreneurs, investors, and industry leaders from The Indus Entrepreneurs (TiE) network, often hosted in cities like Hyderabad.

name: Sunburn Festival Goa
description: Asia's premier electronic dance music (EDM) festival. Held on the beautiful beaches of Goa, it features top international DJs and massive stage productions.

name: Kochi-Muziris Biennale
description: An international exhibition of contemporary art held in Kochi, Kerala. It's the largest art exhibition in India and the first of its kind held in the country.

name: Ahmedabad Heritage Walk
description: A guided walking tour through the historic walled city of Ahmedabad, a UNESCO World Heritage City. Explore the intricate 'pols', 'havelis', and architectural marvels.

name: Chandigarh Literary Fest
description: A celebration of literature and ideas in the 'City Beautiful'. The festival hosts renowned authors, poets, and thinkers for panel discussions, readings, and workshops.

name: Pune International Film Festival (PIFF)
description: An annual film festival that showcases a diverse range of world cinema, with a special focus on films from Maharashtra. Includes competitions and screenings.

name: The Great Indian Food Festival - Delhi
description: A massive gathering of food lovers, featuring culinary delights from all over India. Experience street food, regional cuisines, and gourmet dishes in one place.

name: Mumbai FinTech Festival
description: A conference focusing on the intersection of finance and technology. Keynotes and panels on digital payments, blockchain, insurtech, and the future of banking.

name: International Yoga Festival - Rishikesh
description: While in Rishikesh, many from cities like Delhi attend. A week-long celebration of yoga, featuring classes from world-renowned masters, spiritual talks, and cultural performances.

name: India Bike Week
description: The largest gathering of motorcyclists in India, held in Goa. Features bike showcases, stunt competitions, live music, and brand exhibitions.

name: NASSCOM Technology & Leadership Forum
description: A premier event for the Indian technology industry, focusing on digital transformation, innovation, and future trends. Hosted in Mumbai.

name: Durga Puja Festival
description: A city-wide grand celebration in Kolkata honoring the goddess Durga. The city is adorned with elaborate pandals (temporary structures) and artistic idols. A cultural extravaganza.

name: World Book Fair - New Delhi
description: A nine-day literary event that brings together publishers, authors, and book lovers from all over the world. A major calendar event for the publishing industry.

name: Indian Super League (ISL) - FC Goa Match
description: Experience the thrill of a live football match as FC Goa takes on a rival team in the Hero Indian Super League at their home stadium in Margao.

name: Bangalore Open Air
description: India's biggest heavy metal festival. A haven for rock and metal enthusiasts, featuring top international and domestic bands.

name: Lakme Fashion Week
description: India's premier fashion event, showcasing the latest trends from top designers and emerging talent. Held bi-annually in Mumbai or Delhi.

name: Mysore Dasara
description: A 10-day state festival of Karnataka, with its grandest celebrations in Mysore. Many people from Bangalore travel for the famous Jumboo Savari (procession of elephants).

name: Cyber Security Conclave - Hyderabad
description: A gathering of cybersecurity experts, ethical hackers, and policymakers to discuss the latest threats, trends, and solutions in digital security.

name: Pushkar Camel Fair
description: One of India's most famous traditional festivals. While in Pushkar, it attracts tourists and photographers from nearby cities like Jaipur for the cultural spectacle.

name: India Mobile Congress
description: The largest digital technology event in South Asia, held in Delhi. Showcases the latest in 5G, IoT, AI, and telecommunications technology.

name: Goa Arts and Literature Festival (GALF)
description: A celebration of creative expression, bringing together writers, artists, and thinkers from across India and the world in a non-commercial, intimate setting.

name: Pune Comedy Festival
description: A weekend of laughter featuring a lineup of India's best stand-up comedians. Multiple stages with back-to-back performances.

name: National Organic Food Festival
description: An initiative to promote organic food, featuring exhibitors from across the country. A platform for farmers, retailers, and consumers to connect. Hosted in Delhi.

name: Prithvi Theatre Festival
description: An annual festival celebrating theatre at the iconic Prithvi Theatre in Mumbai. Showcases a mix of new plays and classics from renowned theatre groups.

name: Agile India Conference
description: Asia's largest and most premier conference on Agile software development methods. Hosted in Bangalore, it brings together practitioners and thought leaders.

name: International Health & Fitness Festival (IHFF)
description: A premier event for fitness enthusiasts in Mumbai, featuring bodybuilding competitions, workshops, and exhibitions of health and nutrition products.

name: Ahmedabad International Children Film Festival
description: A film festival dedicated to showcasing high-quality, entertaining, and inspiring films for children and young adults.

name: India Education Fair
description: An exhibition in Kolkata providing a platform for students to interact with representatives from various universities and educational institutions.

name: Tata Steel Literary Meet
description: A prominent literary festival held in cities including Bhubaneswar and Kolkata, featuring conversations with authors, poets, and intellectuals.

name: Indian Gaming Show
description: An international event in Delhi for the gaming industry, showcasing new games, hardware, and e-sports competitions. A hub for developers, publishers, and gamers.

name: Global Investors Meet - Chennai
description: A flagship business event of the Government of Tamil Nadu to attract investment, focusing on sectors like manufacturing, automobiles, and IT.

name: Ziro Festival of Music
description: An iconic outdoor music festival in Arunachal Pradesh. Many attendees travel from cities like Guwahati, creating tour packages for this unique cultural experience.

name: Surajkund International Crafts Mela
description: A vibrant celebration of Indian crafts, handlooms, and cultural heritage near Delhi. Features artisans from all over the country and the world.

name: India Design ID
description: India's definitive design week held in Delhi, featuring exhibitions on architecture, interior design, product design, and installations from leading brands and designers.

name: Hyderabad Literary Festival (HLF)
description: An annual literary event celebrating literature and culture. Each year features a guest nation and focuses on an Indian language, alongside English.

name: Airtel Hyderabad Marathon
description: One of the most popular and challenging city marathons in India, offering full marathon, half marathon, and 10K categories for runners.

name: Navratri Festival Celebrations
description: Ahmedabad is famous for its nine nights of vibrant Garba and Dandiya Raas celebrations. A spectacular display of culture, music, and dance.

name: Auto Expo - The Motor Show
description: Asia's largest automotive show, held biennially near Delhi. Features new vehicle launches, concept cars, and showcases from all major auto manufacturers.

name: Rann Utsav
description: A magnificent cultural festival on the white salt desert of Kutch, Gujarat. Tourists from Ahmedabad and other cities visit for the music, dance, crafts, and stunning landscapes.
